The Ibadan Electricity Distribution Company (IBEDC) on Saturday, commiserated with families of Mr Oladeji Olatunji and Mrs Kemi Adegoke who died on Friday from electrocution. IBEDC in a statement signed by Mr John Ayodele, the IBEDC Chief Operating Officer said the incident happened on Iwo-Adogba road in Ibadan at about 4 pm on Friday. It said investigations had begun to ascertain facts of the case while all necessary protocols and reports have been initiated. “We are currently working with families of the deceased at this difficult period to help provide some measure of succour. “Our team of engineers are already carrying out safety routine maintenance to forestall such occurrences in future,” Ayodele said in the statement.